On 25 March 2021, people rallied at the Capitol in Albany (New York) on the one year anniversary of the 25 March 2020 order to put hospitalized coronavirus positive patients back into nursing homes, which protesters believe is to blame for the spike in nursing home coronavirus deaths. Protesters also rallied against New York Governor who they say prioritized COVID-19 testing for his nearest family, friends, staff during the height of the pandemic in 2020.

notes: On 4 March 2021, about 21 people organized by Direct Action Everywhere staged a 'Shut Down Golden Gates Fields' protest at the racetrack in Berkeley (California) against the mistreatment of horses used for racing and the death of at least five horses at the track in 2021. While 17 demonstrators rallied near the track's entrance, four demonstrators chained themselves together on the track and were later arrested by police. A nearby COVID-19 vaccination site was temporarily shut down due to the demonstration.

On 21 February 2021, more than 100 people rallied outside Tower Theatre in Fresno (California) against the sale to Adventure Church during the COVID-19 pandemic. About seven counter-demonstrators attended.

On 7 February 2021, anti-mask protesters assembled in Belfast (Maine) to protest mask mandates due to the coronavirus pandemic. An individual driving by stopped and got out of her car, engaging the anti-mask protesters. She pulled down her mask and told protesters she worked at a 'COVID-positive' place. When a protester put their phone in front of her face, she took the phone and got in her car and left. Police stepped in and wrote tickets for disorderly conduct for the individual and multiple protesters.
